# Performance rules

## List loaders

- Paginated UIs **MUST** call loaders with `{ limit, offset }` and use the returned `{ books, filteredCount }` — never `paginateAll` + client `.slice()` for the primary list path.
- Canonical example: `loadBookListFiltered` in [`src/lib/library/server/loaders.ts`](mdc:src/lib/library/server/loaders.ts).
- `?all=true` / export paths may fetch the full filtered set; document why in the decision log if the set can exceed ~2k rows.
- **Count + page in one PostgREST call** — `{ count: 'exact' | 'estimated' }` on the data `select`, not a parallel `head: true` count query.
- **Keyword search** — use `books.search_vector` + `.textSearch()` (one round-trip). Do not add author-prelude + `OR` ilike chains for list search.
- **List rows** — use denormalized `author_display` / `publisher_*_display` columns; no nested `book_authors → people` embed on the paginated list path.

## SELECT lists

- Loaders **MUST** use explicit column lists. No `select('*')` except `head: true` count queries.

## Indexes

- Any column in a hot-path `WHERE`, `ORDER BY`, or join filter **MUST** have a matching index in `supabase/migrations/`.
- Prefer partial indexes: `WHERE deleted_at IS NULL` on library tables.
- Full-text list search: GIN on `books.search_vector` (maintained by triggers).
- After adding an index migration: `npm run supabase:db:push:dry` → `npm run supabase:db:push` → `npm run supabase:gen-types`.

## Page `load` budget

- **≤ 4 Supabase round-trips** per page `load` unless documented in the decision log.
- **Corpus totals** — `count: 'estimated'` for display-only “N books” headers; exact count only when business logic requires it.
- **Static vocab** — bible book names from [`bible-book-names.ts`](mdc:src/lib/library/bible-book-names.ts); do not query `bible_books` on every `/library/*` layout navigation.
- Global vocabulary (topic counts, ancient-texts list, `loadPeople` for facets) **MUST** load from sibling `+server.ts` JSON on idle/first open — not on every layout navigation.
- Non-critical book-detail data (topics, coverage rows) **MAY** stream as unawaited promises in `load`; render with `{#await}`.

## Invalidation

- Use `invalidate('app:…')` + matching `depends('app:…')` — not `invalidateAll()` — for library mutations.
- Keys in use: `app:library:facets` (layout series), `app:library:list`, `app:library:book:<uuid>`, `app:library:review`, `app:library:ancient_texts`.

## Auth

- `locals.safeGetSession` → [`resolveSessionUser`](mdc:src/lib/server/auth-session.ts) (`auth.getClaims()` — local JWKS verify when asymmetric signing keys are enabled). Do not call `auth.getUser()` directly from layouts.
- Do not add per-navigation Auth HTTP calls without documenting in the decision log.

## Storage signed URLs

- `SCRIPTURE_IMAGES_SIGNED_URL_TTL` = 24h ([`src/lib/library/storage.ts`](mdc:src/lib/library/storage.ts)); paths are immutable after upload.
- Sign with bounded parallelism via [`signStorageUrlsLimited`](mdc:src/lib/library/sign-storage-urls.ts) — do not unbounded `Promise.all` over hundreds of paths.

## Bundle

- Heavy route components (`@zxing/*`, `pdfjs-dist`, `MultiCombobox`, large forms): **dynamic `import()`** from the page or idle/`open` gates — see [025](mdc:docs/decisions/025-library-bundle-split.md) and [044](mdc:docs/decisions/044-pwa-responsiveness.md).
- Do not add `bits-ui` primitives to [`src/routes/+layout.svelte`](mdc:src/routes/+layout.svelte); use plain markup for chrome dividers.

## Navigation / PWA

- Tab bar: `data-sveltekit-preload-data="hover"` + early `preloadData` on `pointerdown`/`touchstart`; global `preload-code=eager` in [`app.html`](mdc:src/app.html).
- Show [`nav-module-skeleton.svelte`](mdc:src/lib/components/nav-module-skeleton.svelte) while `navigating` — do not leave the previous screen frozen.
- Service worker: **no HTML / mutation cache**; SWR only for static library vocab JSON ([`service-worker.ts`](mdc:src/service-worker.ts)).

## Observability

- HTML responses include `Server-Timing` segments (`auth`, `db`, `total`) from [`hooks.server.ts`](mdc:src/hooks.server.ts). Regress with `npm run test:perf` when credentials are configured.

## Client-heavy forms (batch OCR)

- Do **not** `$derived` / `JSON.stringify` an entire editable row array for submit — build the payload **once** at submit time ([`buildRowsJsonPayload`](mdc:src/lib/library/scripture-batch-upload.ts)).
- Lists with **>50** editable rows: **collapse-by-default** after OCR merge + **windowed** `{#each}` ([`computeRowWindow`](mdc:src/lib/library/scripture-batch-upload.ts)); use `patchRow` for single-row toggles instead of full `rows.map`.
- Long-running OCR/upload pipelines: **sessionStorage draft** ([`scripture-batch-draft.ts`](mdc:src/lib/library/scripture-batch-draft.ts)) + `beforeunload` / parent `beforeNavigate` when dirty.
- Batch saves **>75** rows: client **chunked** `fetch` to `?/createScriptureRefsBatch`; cap parallel file pipelines with [`runWithConcurrency`](mdc:src/lib/library/run-with-concurrency.ts) (default 2).
